  "preFix": {
    "title": "Roast leg of lamb",
    "subtitle": "Studded with garlic and rosemary, served with mint sauce",
    "excerpt": "A whole leg of lamb studded with garlic slivers and rosemary, roasted until pink and carved at the table. The classic British Easter joint.",
    "sourceNotes": "Mrs Beeton, Book of Household Management (1861), Project Gutenberg #10136. Leg of mutton and lamb roasting entries.\n\nEliza Acton, Modern Cookery for Private Families (1845), Project Gutenberg. Roast leg of lamb method.",
    "body": {
      "type": "doc",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "A whole leg of lamb is a generous joint: two kilograms feeds six people easily and asks very little of the cook. The meat is flavourful enough to need only garlic and rosemary pressed into small cuts across the surface.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Pink lamb is better than grey. A probe reading of 60 degrees C at the thickest part gives a warm pink centre; 65 degrees C gives pale pink throughout.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "What you need",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "ingredientsList",
          "attrs": {
            "items": [
              {
                "name": "Lamb leg",
                "unit": "g",
                "amount": 2000,
                "prepNote": null,
                "groupLabel": null,
                "isOptional": false,
                "ingredientId": "cmp49f45e0025rkv4acqg0gkt",
                "ingredientSlug": "lamb-leg"
              },
              {
                "name": "Garlic",
                "unit": "clove",
                "amount": 4,
