              },
              {
                "name": "Chicken stock",
                "unit": "ml",
                "amount": 200,
                "prepNote": null,
                "groupLabel": "For the tin",
                "isOptional": false,
                "ingredientId": "cmp49f8xo00alrkv49cprn7ss",
                "ingredientSlug": "stock-chicken"
              }
            ],
            "defaultServings": 6
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "A paring knife is useful for making clean, deep slits in the meat for the garlic and rosemary.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Method",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 3
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Stud and season",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Make about 16 deep slits across the surface of the lamb with a paring knife. Press a sliver of garlic and a pinch of chopped rosemary into each slit. This is ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "studding",
                      "type": "text",
                      "marks": [
                        {
                          "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                          "attrs": {
                            "termId": "cmpedg44p0000zov49lv5ec9c"
                          }
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "text": ".",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Rub the butter all over the joint and season generously with salt and pepper.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 3
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Roast",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Heat the oven to 200 degrees C fan. Scatter the onion and carrot across the base of the roasting pan, pour over the stock, then set the rack on top. Place the lamb on the rack.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Roast for 20 minutes to colour the surface, then reduce to 180 degrees C. Continue roasting for about 60 more minutes, checking the temperature from 45 minutes onward.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Pull the lamb at 60 degrees C for pink throughout; at 65 degrees C for pale pink; at 72 degrees C for well done.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 3
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Rest and carve",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Transfer to a warm plate and tent with foil. ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Rest",
                      "type": "text",
                      "marks": [
                        {
                          "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                          "attrs": {
                            "termId": "cmp73twkn0001p8v4kyryolap"
                          }
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " for 20 minutes before carving.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Carve parallel to the bone, working in long slices from the rounded top side first, then turning the leg to carve the flatter underside.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "troubleshooter",
          "attrs": {
            "items": [
              {
                "fix": "This is normal and correct for a pink roast. Check the temperature at the thickest part of the muscle, away from the bone.",
                "cause": "The bone conducts heat slowly; the meat nearest it is always the last to cook.",
                "symptom": "The meat near the bone is still very pink when the outside is done"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Use a probe thermometer. Lamb dries out quickly above 70 degrees C.",
                "cause": "Overcooked past 72 degrees C.",
                "symptom": "The joint is dry and tight"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Push each sliver deep enough that it is covered by the meat. Any that sit at the surface will char in the oven.",
                "cause": "The garlic slivers were pushed too shallow or sat proud of the surface.",
                "symptom": "The garlic burnt on the surface"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Add another 100 ml of stock or water to the tin if the juices start to catch.",
                "cause": "The stock evaporated and the vegetables scorched.",
                "symptom": "The pan juices are thick and dark"
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Variations",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Butterflied leg (boned and opened flat) cooks in about 40 minutes at 200 degrees C and gives more brown surface to carve from. Rub the opened surface with a paste of garlic, rosemary, and a little lemon zest before cooking.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Where this dish lives",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Roast leg of lamb arrived at the British Easter table partly because the new season lambs were ready in spring. Victorian cookery writer Mrs Beeton devotes a long section to it in the 1861 edition, recommending a flour dredge before roasting to crisp the surface. The garlic-and-rosemary stud is the twentieth-century French influence that pushed out the older English approach of plain basting.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    "servings": 6,
    "yieldDescription": null,
    "difficulty": "BEGINNER"
  },
